				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Nice to meet you all, and a couple of you, nice to see you again.
<br />
<br />The number #1 reason to make games is self enjoyment, absolutely right. I always like the idea of making NES games with a high degree of passion and indulgence. A big issue seems to keep oneself motivated to make the game and stay focused on it, and not having it get too disorganized, which is understandable for large scale individualistic projects. But I'm glad to hear the value here in the NES, and the bottom line that if you make good games, people will play them.
<br />
<br />I'm liking the advice about planning the whole thing out before you do it. It is very important to sit yourself down and know exactly what you are going to work on and plug away for hours. It's a good feeling.</div>

